They expanded the market because really for the first time there were comics for girls," says Brigid Alverson, a freelance journalist for Comic Book Resources, Publishers Weekly and other publications. She credits publishing company Tokyopop for bringing blockbusters titles like "Sailor Moon" and "Fruits Basket" to a young American female audience.
